cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.CV 

This paper deals with regularized optimization problems in machine learning, specifically the Support Vector Machine (SVM). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves optimization algorithms and complexity analysis, which could fall under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of SVMs in computer vision applications could also place this paper in cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper involves theoretical analysis of solution paths, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
